        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 7:00PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 659 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dowagiac, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dowagiac, Pokagon, Wakelee, and La Grange.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
